<TITLE> 3000 policemen launch special anticrime drive </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 15 (bdnews24.com)At least 3,000 police personnel were deployed across capital Dhaka on Friday as part of specially coordinated operation to improve security, the city police chief said. State minister for home Tanjim Ahmed on Thursday declared the coordinated campaign. "At least three security posts have been deployed at each police station. Women police personnel are also there," Dhaka Metropolitan Police commissioner AKM Shahidul Haque told bdnews24.com late on Friday night. Plainclothes detectives and RAB members are also working, he added. As he was speaking to bdnews24.com, Haque was in Badda Police Station to oversee the operation. The home minister was also on the streets to monitor the operation, he added. Businessman Ashfaq Hossain told bdnews24.com that police checked him and his car papers when he was coming to Malibagh from Banani. Inspector general Noor Mohammad told bdnews24.com on Thursday: "Quite a number of (criminal) incidents happened in the city." This operation is designed to add thrust to the usual work of the law-enforcing agencies, he added. bd
